data.reasoningText:
OK, now the line is:```csharp
var lroDetails = ModelReaderWriter.Write(rehydrationToken, ModelReaderWriterOptions.Json, AzureResourceManagerContext.Default);
return lroDetails["id"];```

`ModelReaderWriter.Write` returns `BinaryData`. And then `lroDetails["id"]` won't work on `BinaryData`. I need to deserialize it properly.

Let me replace the whole line with the proper AOT-safe approach:```csharp
var lroData = ModelReaderWriter.Write(rehydrationToken, ModelReaderWriterOptions.Json, AzureResourceManagerContext.Default);


var lroDetails = JsonSerializer.Deserialize(lroData.ToMemory().Span, ResourceManagerJsonSerializerContext.Default.DictionaryStringString);
return lroDetails["id"];
```

I need to add the necessary using statements for `System.Text.Json` and make sure `Azure.ResourceManager` is in scope, then apply this fix across all four files.

